<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a once a week group of friends that have been playing EQ for over 2 years now, and this particular group for a few months.  We're willing to take risks, but this particular grouping is one we are unpracticed with.<P>Unfortunately, our warrior and our rogue are missing in action for the forseeable future due to AT&T and Luclin ;/  That being the case our group consists of a cleric (me), a wizard, a mage, and a bard, all about 21-23.  <P>It occurred to me that perhaps a workable hunting scenerio is a mini-aoe group, though I know we're hampered by not having an enchanter.  Can anyone suggest to me locations that might work for us to practice in, and/or tactics we should try since we aren't an optimum group for this?<P>Thanks!<P>Serenya, 39.96 cleric of Brell, Tribunal<BR>Velma, 36 cleric of Brell, Fennin (ret.)<BR>Tygerlily, 21 cleric of Bristlebane, Druzzil</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Without the AoE stuns, I don't think you can hack it.  The stuns help to mitigate damage and buy the casters time to get spells off. It's intergral when dealing with pure casters who are doing all the damage.<P>Take my advise with a grain of salt, I've never done a real AoE group below level 45 or without an enchanter.  It seems to me though they go smooter with two enchanters.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aquinas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I agree; I don't see how you can have a successful AoE group without a chanter -- or more specifically, a chanter who's high enough level to chain-cast AE stuns.  The efficiency of AoE hunting comes from killing many mobs at once, and without stuns I don't know how you're going to survive standing in a crowd of aggressive experience-giving mobs.  Particularly when you take into account that, at that level, you probably still have trouble casting if you're getting hit.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some high 30s and low 40s did lower guk, but they had a 52 and 54 enchanter to stun for them.  Whether it could be done with a 44 ENC who knows, but they didnt have issues at all and got incredible exp (About 1 yellow a pull heh)<P>Aladain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShinZed</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A 44 ENC would have no trouble stunning in Lguk, they have all the spells if their research is up to snuff. Nothing in Lguk is all that resistant.<P>For the low level AoE group, you don't need stuns as much as a higher level group, given that your casters can actually withstand a good few rounds of combat if they are decently equipped. Of course, snagging a 20+ enchanter (has 2 stuns) would be a huge boon.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mistmoore yard, kurns tower, sarnak fort in LoIO, maybe paludal.  Try having the bard sing lullaby during the ae.  That's a pretty big taunt and has a side effect of "kinda" being an ae mez.  (Tho very resistable)  I forget what level bards get the ae slow but that's a decent taunt too and has an obvious use in ae.  (It's high 20's I think)  You want the plate-wearing bard tanking everything so you're free to heal the bard and the casters should they get aggro.  Mage rain spells I understand don't generate a lot of aggro.  Wizard will likely be the one you have the most trouble keeping alive.  But being proactive and getting the bard to keep aggro can assure some decent pulls.<P>Don't listen to the people saying a group can't ae without an enchanter.  It's a low 20's group for crying out loud. :P  Even then, we were ae'ing in the grey before the nerf with just me (60 cleric) and a 57 wizard as the only two in the group who could cast an ae spell.  Just test the waters a bit and you'll be fine.  My nec has done ae in crystal caverns and cazic without an enchanter before.  Granted, an enchanter will let you double the size of the pulls but it's still doable.<P>When your ae group gets to upper 20's, 29 for wizards, hit cazic courtyard.  Great ae spot.  You'd think paw would be great too, but the levels there vary too much and the number of casters make it tough to gather all the mobs together before your group has taken a serious beating.  Once you get to 34, especially ae'ers, hit crystal caverns.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thank you everyone for the comments.  We're on hiatus till the New Year, but at that point I think I'll drag the group back out to Mistmoore or maybe CT for aoe practice.  After 2+ years and several avatars, I don't think any of us care if our lowbies die, as long as we're having fun  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"> so this will be an entertaining challenge.<P>Happy Holidays everyone!<P>Serenya, Velma, Tygerlily, Loredena yada yada</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Candail Delour</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">can kite them, heh. make sure everyone has sow or whatever and take turns aoe nuking. <BR>or, since you have a bard, can have him/her mez them for a minuit or so to accumulate aggro then kite them with selo while everyone aoe nukes.  i leveled my wizard alot doing this with a bard and a mage in lake of ill omen through the 20's. also leveled my bard through the 20's this way.<p>[This message has been edited by Candail Delour (edited 12-20-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
